🧠 What is Real-Time Communication?

Real-time communication means:

👉 Data is updated **instantly without refreshing page**

Examples:

✔ Chat apps 💬
✔ Live notifications 🔔
✔ Online gaming 🎮
✔ Live dashboards 📊

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 HTTP vs WebSocket

| Feature    | HTTP             | WebSocket  |
| ---------- | ---------------- | ---------- |
| Connection | Request/Response | Persistent |
| Speed      | Slower           | Faster     |
| Real-time  | ❌                | ✔          |
| Use        | APIs             | Live apps  |

---

🔷 Problem with HTTP

HTTP works like:

```text
Client → Request → Server → Response → Close
```

❌ Not real-time
❌ Needs repeated requests (polling)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 What is WebSocket?

**WebSocket** is a protocol that:

👉 Creates a **persistent connection** between client & server

✔ Two-way communication
✔ Real-time data
✔ No repeated requests

---

🔷 WebSocket Flow

```text
Client ↔ Server (continuous connection)
```

---

🔷 What is Socket.IO?

**Socket.IO** is a library that:

✔ Simplifies WebSocket usage
✔ Works with Node.js
✔ Provides real-time features easily

---

🔷 Install Socket.IO

```bash
npm install socket.io
```

---

🔷 Setup Server

```javascript
const express = require("express");
const http = require("http");
const { Server } = require("socket.io");

const app = express();
const server = http.createServer(app);

const io = new Server(server);

io.on("connection", (socket) => {
  console.log("User connected");

  socket.on("message", (msg) => {
    console.log(msg);
  });
});

server.listen(3000);
```

---

🔷 Client Side Setup

```html
<script src="/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
<script>
  const socket = io();

  socket.emit("message", "Hello Server");
</script>
```

---

🔷 Send & Receive Messages

Server

```javascript
socket.on("chat", (msg) => {
  io.emit("chat", msg);
});
```

---

Client

```javascript
socket.on("chat", (msg) => {
  console.log(msg);
});
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Broadcasting

```javascript
io.emit("message", "Hello everyone");
```

✔ Sends to all clients

---

🔷 Rooms in Socket.IO

```javascript
socket.join("room1");
io.to("room1").emit("message", "Hello Room");
```

✔ Group communication

---

